# GIS Toolbox

Read `AGENTS.md` before substantive work. For git and release workflow, also read `docs/DEVELOPMENT.md`.

**New GIS Widget work:** read `docs/WIDGET_AGENT_PLAYBOOK.md` first, then `docs/WIDGET_AUTHORING.md`.

## Stack

Browser-based GIS toolkit — React 19, Vite, vanilla JS modules under `js/`, React islands under `react/`.

## Code

- Match existing patterns in surrounding files
- Minimize scope — focused changes only
- Reuse existing abstractions; do not reimplement similar logic
- Only add tests when requested or when they add meaningful coverage

## Git (summary)

Local edits on `staging` only. No feature branches. No PRs. User commits and merges via GitHub Desktop. See `.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc`.
